description:
Biography

Nomad is born as the son and heir to the reigning king of "the fire-walled country" on the planet of Pandarve. This area is so remote it's practically impossible to reach by normal means.

To satisfy his curiousity regarding the outside world he leaves his country just to get captured and put to work as a slave in the water mines of Vertiga Bas. This is where he meets Storm with whom he sets up a very succesful escape plan. Once free he decides to join Storm on his travels together with Ember.

Abilities

Nomad is a very agile fighter with a strong physique that he likes to show off. He's an expert in unarmed combat and is considered one of the strongest fighters around.

deck: Also know as Child One, it's a Cosmic Demon, enemy and creator of Gemini
description:
History

Nosferath is a powerfull demonic entity imprisoned eons ago into a "pan-dimension" similar to Limbo. Little or nothing is know about it and it's history, except that it is a creature with immense power that can control the so called "Meta-Impulse" (a scientific name given by Edwig Caine to it's demonic energy).

While searching the secret of superhuman, Edwig Caine start to study magic, and in someway free Nosferath from it's prison. The monster enter the body of a newborn in the International Hospital of Segrate (a city near Milan, in Italy), and it's arrive relase a blast of "Meta-Impulse" that kills any other baby in the hospital and transform into monster all others humans.

Anyway, even if incredibly powerfull, Nosferath was still immature in that children body, and needed aid and protection. When Edwig Cain arrive to the hospital (alongside Italian Militars), he made a pact with the Nosferath: he would take care of the entity, now surnamed "Childe One", and the entity will undisclose to him the secret of the superhumans.

Accepting the pact, Child One resurrect with meta-impulse 5 newborns, and Mr. Illusion save them from the monster and take them to Edwig Cain. The 5 babies will become the members of Gemini.

However, Edwig Caine try to trick the devil, closing Child One in containment technology and slowing it's growing process: after more than 20 years, Child One was still a baby and can't reach the full extend of it's powers.

When Front start to investigate about the origins of his team, Child One lure Edwig Caine assistant, Alma Zareth, into freeing it in exchange of great power. With the help of Alma Zareth [now Alma Matrix] and Mr. Illusion, Nosferath fight Gemini and nearly killed all of them, but it's easly surprised and defeated by The Voyager, who cage it again in it cosmic prison.

Note

The true mother of the baby called "Child One" (the real baby, killed and possessed) was called Laura Di Giovanni. She lived in paranoia from that day, chased by nightmare and horrible vision, till she was killed by Mr. Illusion on order of the Child One itself. Howaver, the mind of Mr. Illusion is so confused that he think the woman died from brain cancer.

deck: British Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D.
description:
History

Marvel Italia

A British Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D., Lancelot [the real name is still unknown] was charged to evalue the Gemini Team, to give it authorization to became operative. After watching one of their training session, he denied the permission, considering the team unready and too instable.

When Edwig Cain, creator of the Gemini Project, deploy on the field the team inspite of the S.H.I.E.L.D. deny, Agent Lancelot start to investigate on the true motivation of the project. When the leader of the Team, Front, apparently kill Cain and go rogue, Lancelot follow him and durring their first confrontation, shot the hero in the face with a blaster-gun, disfiguring him.

Trying to infiltrate in to the Gemini headquarter, Lancelot risk his life when the Nosferath and Alma Matrix launch thier attack, being saved only by the fortuitous intervention of Iron Man.

After that, he and Front make a truce and, alongside Mr. Illusion, go to the rescue of Gemini and fight the Nosferath. After the terrible battle, Agent Lancelot leave Italia and the Gemini team, still doubtufull about them, but willfull to give them a chance.

Powers

Agent Lancelot have no real superpowers. However, as a trained Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D. with both experience on field and years of service, he is an expert in many form of combat, weapon and technical skills. Also, he is usually equipped with standard S.H.I.E.L.D.'s Agent equipment, includig protective suite and hand blaster guns.

deck: Expert in biology and genetics turned demon
description:
History

Marvel Italia

According to S.H.I.E.L.D. datafile, Alma Zareth was one of world highest expert in Artificial Intelligence, and have worked for all her life with former M.I.5 member and scientis Edwig Caine, aiding and supporting him in raising the five Gemini children and the formation of Gemini Team.

However, she was well aware of the secret of Gemini, the "Meta-Impulse" and the so called "Child One", the Nosferath, keeped in cage in the basement of the Vera Croce base.

When Front start to investigate the truth and seemingly to kill Edwing Caine, Alma first substitute him as official director of the Gemini Project, and after that she free the Child One and aid it to take control of the Vera Croce Base and capture Suede, Grip, Mandala and Balance.

When Mr. Illusion drag Front into a trap and the five children where reunited, Alma, now turned Alma Matrix by the power of Nosferath, prepare herself to kill the heroes for her master. Instead, Nosferath attack and devour her, using her energy to restore it true form.

Powers & Notes

While Alma Matrix seem to have a large set of powers, there are no prove that Nosferath really give here something. While she receive a full body armor, blade that spurt from his wrist, and her hand glow often with energy and other things, she have never used any of them against anyone. So it's possible that Nosferath, planning to kill and devour her, never give her some true power.

As Alma Zareth, she was a stunning beautifull readhead with high intellect and experience in various field: while officially expert only in A.I., a life of work and study with Ediwg Cain, expert in superhuman and supernatural have given her a quite vast rang of knwledge in many field

deck: Stage Illusionist turned Superpowered Minion by the Nosferath
description:
History

Marvel Italia

Little or nothing is known about the life of Mr. Illusion.

He was a normal stage illusionist, who get involved into the "Meta-Impulse" explosion created by the Nosferath at the "International Hospital of Segrate".

While all the babies caught by the explosion dies and other people, including the Italian Militar rushed for help, where muted in horrible monster, Mr. Illusion receive some real superpowers, including an unstable telekinesis, illusion and some degree of magic.

However, his mind suffer the transformation sparede to his body, and his perception of reality become twisted. Under the guidance and order of his "master", the Nosferath, Mr. Illusion save from the monsters the five children who will become the Gemini team, delivering them to Edwig Cain.

The life of Mr. Illusion after that event is clouded in mistery. It's known that the Nosferath had, over the years, used him for horrible task, guiding him with nightmare and obsessivie vision. One of that task have been killing the true mother or the Nosferath host, Laura Di Giovanni, and act he dosen't remember, sure that the woman died from brain cancer. Confused and affected by mental illness, Mr. Illusion pass his life between poverty and alcool dependency.

Reached by Agent Lancelot and Front searching for the truth about the Nosferath, Mr. Illusion allied with them, guiding the heroes to the Nosferath lair, only to betray them in the final confrontation.

After the defeat of the Nosferath, Mr. Illusion disappear, leaving no trace.

Powers

The exact extent and nature of Mr. Illusion's Powers, as for his whole life, are quite confused and not clear. He have show a good degree in telekinesis [rising in the air several people at once] and a good ability in creating solid illusions. However, since the origins of his powers are inherently magical, his claim to have also magical abilities may be true.

deck: Italian Reporter
description:
History

Marvel Italia

Carlo Paci is an inquisitive and determined journalist and reporter which lead both TV and Radio shows. His style is usually that of the anti-conspiracy and anti-corporative reporter, which service are highly critics against government, foreign agency such as the S.H.I.E.L.D. and so on, and he have show more than one time a quite disdain for superheroes. When Gemini start it's operation on Italian soil, Carlo Paci openly attack the project and their operation in various TV Service, and also nterviewing Alma Zareth, he storm her with inquisitive and nasty questions about hidden secret of Edwig Caine.

Anyway, she affirm to have nothing against superheroes, but that he only search the truth. For this reason, he is the only one who aid Front in searching evidence of the truth about Gemini origins, and also help him to find Mr. Illusion.

In the end, he receive file with the whole truth from Front, but decide to give him and his team a chance: he keep the documents for himself, waiting to see if Gemini his a good or bad thing for Italy.

Note

Carlo Paci is a smoker, and is never seen without a lighted cigarette

deck: Cosmic Law-Enforcer, Symbol of Equilibrium
description:
History

Marvel Italia

The Voyager is a sort of cosmic law enforcer, who travel the space for serve the Law and the Equilibrium. He have appeared in two form: a giant humanoid insect with giant wings while traveling in space and a more human form with cloack and energy spear when on earth, in human host.

On the earth is human host is a young boy, son of a Magistrato [italian legale role corresponding to State/District Attorney in U.S.A.] killed by Mafia thug with a gunshot to the head some moments before The Voyager reach the Earth. The Voyager was able to sense some similarity between itslef and the dead boy, being both "Servant of the Law", and so resurrect him as it's host [even if it's not clear how much of the human personality is still awake].

The objective of The Voyager on Earth was to capture Nosferath, imprisoning it again and forever in it's mystical prison, and also clean the planet from all the Meta-Impulse Infected People. For being sure to not fail, it carrie a cosmic time-bomb set to destroy the Earth in case of failure.

Anyway, after easly defeating and capture Nosferath, it sense some justice in Gemini members [which are all "Meta-Impulse Infected"], and value "against the Law and Justice" to destroy them, so it spare the team giving them the chance to use their powers for Justice.

Than it leave the Earth

Powers

The Voyager seem have some sort of Cosmic Power, able to travel in space and easly defeat powerful demonic entities such as Noferath. The exact nature and range of thier divine powers are unknown.

Notes

It's not clear if the humanoid insect form The Voyager used in space was it true form or only that of it last host.

Also it's not clear if it really resurrect in some form it's current human host, or if it simply inhabit his dead body.

Alongside the Gemini team, The Voyager seem spare the life to villainous Mr. Illusion, another "Meta-Impulse Infected", for some inesplicable reason [perhaps the villain flee from the scene off panel, but still The Voyager dosen't pursuit him for accomplish it's objective]

deck: Former Militar, Scientist and father of the Gemini Project
description:
History

Marvel Italia

Former Militar and Scientist, Edwig Cain was an expert in many scientific field, including some non conventional one [such as some form of necromancy]

Obsessed by his research of the "secret of superpower" for creating super-heroes and mutation, and frustrated by a life of failure, Edwig Cain resort to his last chance, using magic to manipulate a "semi-scientific energy", the Meta-Impulse. In doing so, he involountary release the Nosferath and destroy the "International Hospital of Segrate".

Instead of fight the cosmic demon, Edwig Cain made a pact with him, offering to the creature hide and protection in exchange of the secret of superpower. The Nosferath give him 5 baby, resurrected by it's energy, and the baby would grown up as the member of Gemini.

Many years after that event, the Nosferath broke free from his hiding place, that Edwig Cain have transformed over the years into a containment prison. Kidnapping the scientist, the creature aim to capture and kill all the one that have been empowered by it's "Meta-Impulse".

Durring the final fight between the heroes and the Nosferath, Edwig Cain lost is life, drained by the power of the cosmic creature.


Note

For some unknown reason, Edwig Cain raises one of the "meta-impulse babies" as his own son, and so he share is surename with Gabriel Cain, Front, Leader of the Gemini, which result being his legal son.

deck: European Version of the Super-Adaptoid
description:
History

European version of the Super-Adaptoid, crated by anarchic A.I.M. division gone rogue, and deployed usually in highly poplated area for random killing, in order to create chaos or as act of terrorism.

The Euro-Adaptoid can shapeshif, rearranging it structure to assume camouflaged form, such as a suitcase or a trashcan, to lure possible host. The Euro-Adaptoid usually fuse it's structures with that of an human, using him/her as an energy battery. It's sistem tie directly with the nervouse system of the victim, so any damage done to the Euro-Adaptoid relase a rush of pain in it's host.

There are no clear way to de-attach the robot from it's victim, but the Euro-Adaptoid dosen't need to consume the whole reserve of energy before discharging it, so often pass from an human to the next, releasing the first while still alive.

One Euro-Adaptoid was deployed in the middle of the Subway of Milan [Italy], hidden as a suitcase. It's mission was to kill 25 random people. After it's activation, it take a children as host, and after a brief fight with Gemini, release the children to capture Balance. However, Front attack the robot, offering itself as new host, but the Euro-Adaptoid cannot overcome the super-physiology of Gabriel Caine combined with his support-A.I, REVO, and collapse.
name: Euro-Adaptoid
